  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Executive Mechanical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description &amp; Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Duties &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist the Team Leader and Job Captain in the performance of their duties</li>\n  <li>Supervise the other design drafting team</li>\n  <li>Ensure quality and accuracy of designs</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with project Design Criteria/Client Brief/Approved Concept</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with relevant design standards and office standards</li>\n  <li>Attend and participate in design meetings</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with ISO Quality Procedure Manual</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>A bachelor’s degree in mechanical engineering recognised by Professional Engineers Board.</li>\n  <li>Entry level with some consultancy internship experience are welcome to apply</li>\n  <li>3 years and above design experience in consultancy firm would be advantageous</li>\n  <li>Must have prior hands-on design experience in the design of ACMV, Fire and Hydraulic services for large scale building projects</li>\n  <li>Experience in Rail and infrastructure projects and data centre an advantage</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Additional Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Good interpersonal and communication skills</li>\n  <li>Must be fully familiar with local and international codes</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience with relevant engineering software and BIM</li>\n  <li>Must be able to work independently</li>\n  <li>Must have a good understanding of unit costs of the MEP services in various types of projects</li>\n</ul>",
